  "text": "GameSpot may receive revenue from affiliate and advertising partnerships for sharing this content and from purchases through links. If you like Lego Technic and Batman, you'll want to check out Walmart's deal on the Batcycle set before its gone. The 641-piece Lego Batcycle is up for grabs for only $30. This was a Cyber Monday deal, but it's still available on November 4. Based on the Batcycle from the 2022 film starring Robert Pattinson, the Lego Technic Batcycle normally sells for $50, and it's sold out at all retailers except for Walmart. Walmart has a few other notable Cyber Monday Lego deals that are still available as of December 4, including Darth Vader's Helmet for only $49 (was $80) and Minecraft's Sword Outpost for $30 (was $45).Lego Technic - The Batman Batcycle (641 pieces) -- $30 ($50)Lego Star Wars - Darth Vader Helmet (834 pieces) -- $49 ($80)Lego Minecraft - The Sword Outpost (427 pieces) -- $30 ($45)Lego Disney: Stitch Figure (730 pieces) -- $52 ($65)Lego City - Space Explorers 3-in-1 Super Pack (426 pieces) -- $20 ($32) Lego Technic: The Batman Batcycle (641 Pieces) $30 (was $50) Lego's Technic sets are usually based on real cars and motorcycles, but occasionally the designs recreate popular vehicles from movies such as the Batcycle from the 2022 film The Batman. This is a more complex build than the average Lego set with similar piece counts, but it serves as a good introduction to the Technic line and is recommended for kids ages nine and up.Throughout the build, you'll create \"functional\" steering and suspension systems as well as an articulating H4 engine, which connects to the back wheel with help of the chain drive.This is a pretty decent-sized display model; the completed build is 13 inches long, 6.5 inches tall, and 4.5 inches wide.There's also a Lego Technic build of the Batmobile from The Batman. The 1,360-piece Batmobile originally retailed for $100, but it's no longer in production, which means you typically need to spend a bit more to get the Batmobile from a reseller. At the moment, the Lego Technic Batmobile is available for $135 on Amazon. Lego Batman Construction Figure \u0026 Bat-Pod Bike (713 Pieces) $52 (was $65) If you prefer the Bat-Pod from The Dark Knight, Amazon has the Batman Construction Figure and Bat-Pod Bike set for 20% off, dropping the price from $65 down to $52. This is the best price yet for this cool 713-piece kit that released in August.This is part of the Lego DC Batman line, so the Bat-Pod build isn't nearly as in-depth mechanically. That said, you will build stud shooters for Batman to deploy when he's attached to the bike.The 10-inch Batman figure is one of the newest additions to Lego's fun series of buildable superhero action figures. Construction Figures are multi-jointed, so you can move Batman's arms, legs, and hips to create different poses. This isn't the first Batman Construction Figure. Last year, Lego released a figure based on the Caped Crusader's appearance in Batman Returns. The Batman Returns Construction Figure is on sale for $26.39 (was $33) at Amazon. Got a news tip or want to contact us directly? Email news@gamespot.com",
